Choose any Image you want to make into an icon
If it has solid background open in GIMP
Convert Background to Alpha
Crop Image to Content
Scale to at least 160x160px or any multitude of that
Export as .png
Open in Inkscape
Set Document Size to 160x160px or the multitude of resolution you scaled to
Create rectangle with Rectangle Tool
Set Position to 0,0 and Size to 160,160 or the multitude of resolution of the image
Turn on Fill (color RGBA: fafafaff)
Turn on Stroke (White RGBA: fafafaff, Blue RGBA: 00a8e8ff, Black RGBA: 090909ff, Stroke Width 12px times the multitude of resolution you scaled to)
Moove Icon Layer to foreground
Scale Icon to fit (This is why you create the Background, even if you will not use it)
Center Icon
If no Background is needed, moove cectangle out of document area.
Export at 160x160px as Iconhyperlinkreference(eg.Website,YouTube,etc.)-160x160.png
